goleta = readr::read_csv("data/uscities.csv") %>%
  st_as_sf(coords = c("lng", "lat"), crs = 4326) %>%
  st_transform(5070) %>%
  filter(city == "Goleta") %>%
  st_buffer(5000)
## Parsed with column specification:

bb = goleta %>%
  st_bbox() %>%
  st_as_sfc() %>%
  st_as_sf() %>%
  elevatr::get_elev_raster(z = 13) 
## Warning in sp::proj4string(locations): CRS object has comment, which is lost in
## output
## Warning in sp::proj4string(locations): CRS object has comment, which is lost in
## output

## output
## Mosaicing & Projecting
## Note: Elevation units are in meters.
## Note: The coordinate reference system is:
##  +proj=aea +lat_0=23 +lon_0=-96 +lat_1=29.5 +lat_2=45.5 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs
ele = crop(bb, goleta)

goleta_ele = plot(ele, main="Elevation of Goleta")

#writeRaster(goleta_ele, filename = "data/goleta_ele.tif", overwrite = TRUE)

raster(ele)
## class      : RasterLayer 
## dimensions : 1272, 1272, 1617984  (nrow, ncol, ncell)
## resolution : 7.864357, 7.864357  (x, y)
## extent     : -2157752, -2147749, 1530382, 1540386  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
## crs        : +proj=aea +lat_0=23 +lon_0=-96 +lat_1=29.5 +lat_2=45.5 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs
FUN = function(x) { ifelse(x <= 0,NA,1)}


ele2 = calc(ele, FUN)

mask = bb *ele2
## Warning in bb * ele2: Raster objects have different extents. Result for their
## intersection is returned
layer1 = plot(ele2, col = viridis::viridis(500), main="Mask") 

layer2 = plot(mask, col = viridis::viridis(500), main="elevation")

quarts = cellStats(mask, fivenum)

rcl = data.frame(quarts[1:4], quarts[2:5], 1:4)

reclassify(mask, rcl, include.lowest=TRUE) %>%
  plot(col = viridis::viridis(6), main="topo.bounds")
